2 SENATE BILL 20
1 (c) (1) IN THIS SUBSECTION, “CONSUMER PRICE INDEX FOR ALL URBAN
2 CONSUMERS” MEANS THE INDEX PUBLISHED MONTHLY BY THE BUREAU OF LABOR
3 STATISTICS OF THE U.S. DEPARTMENT OF LABOR THAT IS THE UNITED STATES
4 CITY AVERAGE OF ALL ITEMS IN A BASKET OF CONSUMER GOODS AND SERVICES.
5 (2) THE PERCENTAGE GROWTH IN THE CONSUMER PRICE INDEX FOR
6 ALL URBAN CONSUMERS SHALL BE DETERMINED BY COMPARING THE AVERAGE OF
7 THE INDEX FOR THE 12 MONTHS ENDING ON THE PRECEDING JUNE 30 TO THE
8 AVERAGE OF THE INDEX FOR THE PRIOR 12 MONTHS
9 (3) For fiscal year 2026 and each fiscal year thereafter, the Governor shall
10 include in the annual budget bill an appropriation from the Transportation Trust Fund of
11 at least $80,533,314 to the program for statewide program operations.
12 (4) FOR FISCAL YEAR 2027 AND EACH FISCAL YEAR THEREAFTER,
13 THE APPROPRIATION REQUIRED UNDER PARAGRAPH (3) OF THIS SUBSECTION
14 SHALL BE INCREASED BY THE AMOUNT THAT EQUALS THE PRODUCT OF
15 MULTIPLYING:
16 (I) THE AMOUNT REQUIRED UNDER THIS SUBSECTION TO BE
17 INCLUDED IN THE ANNUAL BUDGET BILL FOR THE PRIOR FISCAL YEAR FOR THE
18 PROGRAM; AND
19 (II) THE LESSER OF:
20 1. THE PERCENTAGE GROWTH IN THE CONSUMER
21 PRICE INDEX FOR ALL URBAN CONSUMERS; OR
22 2. 5%.
23 (5) IF THERE IS A DECLINE OR NO GROWTH IN THE CONSUMER PRICE
24 INDEX FOR ALL URBAN CONSUMERS, THE APPROPRIATION REQUIRED UNDER THIS
25 SUBSECTION SHALL BE EQUAL TO THE AMOUNT OF THE APPROPRIATION FOR THE
26 PRIOR FISCAL YEAR.
27 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect July
28 1, 2025.

